16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280 of Title 59, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
21 Community Health Workers Act".
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280.1 of Title 59, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 12167 Page 1

1 As used in the Oklahoma Community Health Workers Act:
2 1. "Certified community health worker" means a community health
3 worker to whom the State Department of Health has issued a
4 certificate to practice as a certified community health worker in
5 this state;
6 2. "Community health worker" means a frontline public health
7 worker who has a shared understanding of and is a trusted member of
8 the community being served; and
9 3. "Department" means the State Department of Health.
10 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280.2 of Title 59, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. The State Department of Health shall establish a certificate
14 for community health workers. This certification shall be
15 voluntary.
16 B. A certified community health worker may:
17 1. Serve as a liaison between health and social services and
18 the community to facilitate access to services and improve the
19 quality and cultural competence of service delivery;
20 2. Assist in identifying and communicating gaps in current
21 community and health care resources; and
22 3. Build individual and community capacity by increasing health
23 knowledge and self-sufficiency through a range of activities such as
24
