1 outr each, community education, coaching, mentoring, social support,
2 and advocacy.
3 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280.3 of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The State Commissioner of Health shall promulgate rules to:
7 1. Adopt a set of standards for the approval of certified
8 community health workers' initial coursework or curriculum;
9 2. Establish examination administration requirements for the
10 Department or one or more designees;
11 3. Define minimum qualifications for applicants to be
12 certified; and
13 4. Establish the criteria for granting, denying, suspending,
14 and revoking a certificate to protect public health and safety.
15 B. The Commissioner may also promulgate rules necessary for the
16 proper administration and enforcement of the Oklahoma Community
17 Health Workers Act which allow for reciprocity agreements with:
18 1. The Indian Health Service;
19 2. Tribal Contract or Compact Health Centers;
20 3. Urban Indian Health Centers; and
21 4. Tribal health systems.
22 C. The Commissioner shall prescribe fees for the certified
23 community health worker examination, initial certification, and
24 certification renewal.
